1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:11,537
=The Moment I Met You=

2
00:00:11,537 --> 00:00:14,937
=Episode 13=

3
00:00:33,679 --> 00:00:34,799
You won't show any mercy?

4
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:36,200
The proof is undeniable.

5
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,119
Why keep her alive?

6
00:00:45,079 --> 00:00:46,000
Chu Yunchang!

7
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,119
Let's see you talk your way
out of this one.

8
00:00:59,119 --> 00:01:00,600
He has to die. There's no other way.

9
00:01:01,359 --> 00:01:02,479
Nobody touches him!

10
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:04,159
Chang, listen.

11
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:06,500
He saw us bring the money into the shop.

12
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,120
He has to die.

13
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:08,439
Yeah, he has to go.

14
00:01:08,850 --> 00:01:09,969
It's fine.

15
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,680
We were wearing masks

16
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:13,560
at the time.

17
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:14,840
But...

18
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,400
I've already found the Sacred Token.

19
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,159
We'll be free of this life very soon.

20
00:01:18,799 --> 00:01:19,400
But...

21
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,439
My dear.

22
00:01:21,319 --> 00:01:22,879
Let the young people

23
00:01:22,879 --> 00:01:25,120
handle their own problems.

24
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:28,840
We should focus on returning

25
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:30,640
this stolen money.

26
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,000
You'd better know what you're doing.

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,640
Fine.

28
00:01:44,599 --> 00:01:46,159
Don't think a quick wardrobe change

29
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:48,560
hides the fact that you knocked him out.

30
00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:50,200
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,200
I...

32
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,159
Um...

33
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:57,439
Buyu!

34
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:06,200
Chang?

35
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,719
What happened with those two thieves?

36
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:15,120
My uncle was kidnapped.

37
00:02:16,039 --> 00:02:18,280
The kidnappers told me
to leave the ransom

38
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,159
at the flower shop before sunset.

39
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,919
What? You ran into them?

40
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:25,800
Did you have a fight?

41
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:28,719
So those two were the kidnappers?

42
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,240
Where am I?

43
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,919
What is this place?

44
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:38,759
When I found you at the flower shop,

45
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,159
you were all alone.

46
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:42,840
So, I brought you back here.

47
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:50,159
Why didn't you report this?

48
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:52,039
The last time I called the guards,

49
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:54,039
it only made Rong suspicious.

50
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,680
Then, Luo Wushuang

51
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,919
locked me in a cell for days.

52
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:01,879
Besides, my uncle doesn't
trust constables,

53
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:04,240
so my aunt told me not to report it.

54
00:03:04,486 --> 00:03:05,125
How can you

55
00:03:05,125 --> 00:03:06,926
distrust the Imperial Court's officers?

56
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,190
By handling it this way,

57
00:03:08,212 --> 00:03:10,212
you're only emboldening those criminals!

58
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:15,560
By the way,

59
00:03:16,039 --> 00:03:19,280
why were you wearing
those night-clothes earlier?

60
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,280
With Uncle gone,

61
00:03:24,919 --> 00:03:27,439
there are only
three women left in the house.

62
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,919
I was scared to death.

63
00:03:29,159 --> 00:03:31,000
So I thought

64
00:03:31,159 --> 00:03:33,479
I'd put on dark clothes
and stay close by

65
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,840
to see if I could find any clues.

66
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,159
Hold on.

67
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:43,639
Why would the thieves
leave the ransom at the shop?

68
00:03:44,159 --> 00:03:45,479
What if you called the guards?

69
00:03:47,039 --> 00:03:48,919
How should I know
what they were thinking?

70
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,120
Maybe they thought
the most dangerous place

71
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:54,159
was actually the safest.

72
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,240
Buyu.

73
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,280
I'm sorry.

74
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,520
After everything

75
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,479
we've been through,

76
00:04:05,039 --> 00:04:07,520
your apology only proves that
you don't trust me.

77
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:09,680
Chang.

78
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:11,280
We're getting married soon.

79
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:13,400
Your burdens are my burdens now.

80
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,890
If something like this happens again,

81
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,040
don't try to face it all on your own.

82
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,639
I know

83
00:04:28,639 --> 00:04:30,079
you're still hiding things from me.

84
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,079
But it's not your fault.

85
00:04:33,639 --> 00:04:35,360
It just means I haven't done enough

86
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,399
to make you feel like you can trust me.

87
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,240
I'll wait.

88
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,759
I'll wait for the day

89
00:04:41,399 --> 00:04:43,160
you can finally trust me completely.

90
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,199
Go on.

91
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,800
Husband.

92
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:57,839
My dear.

93
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:01,639
Drink your tea.

94
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,480
Thank you.

95
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,000
Careful, it's hot.

96
00:05:07,199 --> 00:05:08,879
Anything you give me is sweet.

97
00:05:08,879 --> 00:05:09,820
I can never be too hot.

98
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,839
Rong, what are you doing?

99
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,480
Oh, you're back.

100
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,439
Can't you see?

101
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:15,720
I'm making tea for my husband.

102
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,600
Are you two alright?

103
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,920
Are you looking for trouble?

104
00:05:19,962 --> 00:05:20,375
(A World Without Thieves)

105
00:05:20,399 --> 00:05:21,160
Who was the one

106
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,560
threatening to divorce Anran?

107
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,360
You two are quite the pair.

108
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:28,439
I didn't realize
how much trouble Anran went through.

109
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:29,580
I was just talking nonsense.

110
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:30,959
Anran,

111
00:05:31,079 --> 00:05:32,120
don't hold it against me.

112
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:34,000
It was my fault for being inconsiderate.

113
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,560
From now on, before I do anything,

114
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,319
I'll be sure to tell you first.

115
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,839
That's a good boy.

116
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,800
All right, that's enough.

117
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:42,079
It's too mushy.

118
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,759
- Father-in-law.
- Anran.

119
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:46,825
- Father!
- Rong.

120
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:48,399
Yu, you're back too.

121
00:05:48,399 --> 00:05:49,040
Father.

122
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,519
Look who's here.

123
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,000
(Mao Jixian, Chief of the Probe Corps)
Uncle Mao, now that your name is cleared

124
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,879
and you've been reinstated,
congratulations.

125
00:06:00,212 --> 00:06:01,120
(Mao Jixian, Chief of the Probe Corps)

126
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,439
I should thank Commissioner Luo

127
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:04,160
and Director Liu too.

128
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,639
Don't just stand there. Take a seat.

129
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:07,590
- Have a seat.
- All right.

130
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,279
Uncle Mao,

131
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,800
you should really thank

132
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,759
your wonderful son-in-law.

133
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,000
Yes, you're right.

134
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,120
My good son-in-law, thank you so much.

135
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,240
It's part of my duty.

136
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,879
Yu, Hu Mei'er is eliminated,

137
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:25,340
and the kidnappings have been solved.

138
00:06:25,439 --> 00:06:26,639
You can finally rest easy.

139
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,199
Thank you.

140
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:34,959
We should have a victory feast today.

141
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:37,030
Wushuang, since you're here,
why don't you join us?

142
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,240
I'll have to pass, Uncle Mao.

143
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,199
The truth is,

144
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,525
I came today

145
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:41,485
to tell you something.

146
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,480
What is it?

147
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:45,519
I have confirmed

148
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:48,480
that Chu Yunchang is the Jade Squirrel.

149
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:56,439
Wushuang.

150
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,290
The last time you accused Chu Yunchang,

151
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,680
you didn't have enough evidence

152
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,759
and a suspect was killed.

153
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,399
You'd better be sure this time.

154
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,199
I saw it with my own eyes.

155
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,279
Buyu,

156
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,399
what do you think?

157
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,240
Buyu.

158
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:21,360
In the past, you would've blamed us
for having no proof

159
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,680
and for wrongly accusing Yunchang.

160
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,120
Why are you so quiet this time?

161
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:28,680
Wushuang.

162
00:07:29,090 --> 00:07:30,199
Do you have any evidence?

163
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,079
I have a witness.

164
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:36,000
Your brother-in-law, Xu Anran.

165
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:42,639
The night before we arrived,

166
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:44,800
the Jade Squirrel
and the Nine-Tailed Fox were fighting.

167
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,680
You must have seen her, right?

168
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,000
Anran.

169
00:07:49,319 --> 00:07:51,240
Did you really see
the Jade Squirrel's face?

170
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:53,319
Yes.

171
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,240
Before I was knocked out,

172
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,759
I saw her clearly.

173
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,120
Coroner Xu.

174
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,360
Tell Buyu now.

175
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,879
Is the Jade Squirrel
actually Chu Yunchang?

176
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,319
No.

177
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:10,959
What?

178
00:08:12,879 --> 00:08:13,600
Constable Luo.

179
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,639
The Jade Squirrel is
definitely not Chu Yunchang.

180
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:20,240
I have never seen that face before.

181
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:21,519
Xu Anran!

182
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,279
How can you lie
through your teeth like that?

183
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,759
Why are you protecting the Jade Squirrel?

184
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:28,560
Luo Wushuang.

185
00:08:28,879 --> 00:08:30,079
Be reasonable.

186
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:32,080
Even if you have
a grudge against Chu Yunchang

187
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,279
and want to frame her,

188
00:08:33,519 --> 00:08:35,559
there is no need
to drag my husband into this.

189
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,600
If you keep making
accusations against him,

190
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,879
I won't let it slide.

191
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,440
You...

192
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:44,080
Why does the whole Mao family
side with criminals?

193
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:48,200
This is ridiculous!

194
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,639
(A World Without Thieves)
Wushuang! Wushuang!

195
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,039
Anran.

196
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:56,080
Are you certain
the Jade Squirrel wasn't Chu Yunchang?

197
00:08:57,039 --> 00:08:57,799
Father.

198
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:58,840
I am

199
00:09:00,759 --> 00:09:01,440
very certain.

200
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:08,440
Let's eat.

201
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:10,799
We're here to thank Squire Mei

202
00:09:10,799 --> 00:09:12,440
for saving my brother-in-law's life.

203
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,720
It was nothing.

204
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,960
Please tell Coroner Xu and Rong

205
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,600
that it was my pleasure.

206
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,679
Tell them

207
00:09:17,679 --> 00:09:19,240
not to worry about it.

208
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,840
But this was my father's idea.

209
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:22,679
Your father?

210
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,279
It means my family

211
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,440
finally approves of us.

212
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,440
You don't seem happy.

213
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,559
No, I'm thrilled.

214
00:09:33,799 --> 00:09:35,600
It just all happened so fast.

215
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,120
I honestly thought

216
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,320
we'd have to go through
a million trials first.

217
00:09:40,399 --> 00:09:41,879
Why would you jinx us like that?

218
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,759
Maybe I should go get some new clothes...

219
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,000
and some new jewelry?

220
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,120
I'll go get things ready.

221
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,039
All right.

222
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:58,279
I should head back to duty.

223
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,600
(Finally, I caught you!)

224
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:10,600
(Oh, Mao Buyu.)

225
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,420
(Instead of working cases
at the Gate Bureau,)

226
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,759
(you're here every day
flirting with a girl.)

227
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:16,879
(If I report this)

228
00:10:16,879 --> 00:10:19,519
(to Wushuang with a little extra spice,)

229
00:10:19,879 --> 00:10:21,559
(she might get so angry)

230
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:23,519
(that her love for you
turns to pure hate.)

231
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:27,320
(Then, my so-called master
will meet an early grave.)

232
00:10:55,759 --> 00:10:57,159
Are you all right, sir?

233
00:10:58,559 --> 00:10:59,159
I...

234
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:01,279
Thank you for helping, Miss.

235
00:11:02,279 --> 00:11:03,240
I am Luo Wuxia.

236
00:11:03,639 --> 00:11:04,720
May I ask your name?

237
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,399
It's nothing worth mentioning.

238
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,159
Miss! Wait!

239
00:11:10,519 --> 00:11:13,120
The girls in the Capital
really are something else.

240
00:11:14,879 --> 00:11:15,840
Please, come in.

241
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,120
Welcome, welcome!

242
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,380
- Squire Mei, Mrs. Mei.
- Please.

243
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,250
Please, have a seat.

244
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:21,039
Madam.

245
00:11:21,039 --> 00:11:22,080
Sit, please.

246
00:11:23,519 --> 00:11:24,159
Chang.

247
00:11:24,159 --> 00:11:25,960
I'll take you out for a stroll later.

248
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,000
Chang.

249
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,399
Come and sit down.

250
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,159
Here.

251
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:37,399
Let me propose a toast.

252
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:41,240
Squire Mei, thank you
for rescuing my son-in-law.

253
00:11:41,559 --> 00:11:42,159
Cheers.

254
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,639
Thank you, Squire Mei.

255
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,840
You're too kind.

256
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,000
Don't mention it, Master Mao.

257
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,879
Mrs. Mei, this toast is for you.

258
00:11:50,399 --> 00:11:51,559
You're very kind, Madam Xu.

259
00:11:56,879 --> 00:11:58,240
Squire Mei, here.

260
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,159
Please, don't be so formal.

261
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:09,480
Come.

262
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:09,840
Father.

263
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,480
This is perfect.

264
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:12,240
I want to marry Chang.

265
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:16,519
I want to make her my wife,
no matter what.

266
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:17,919
Wait, are you...

267
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,360
Are you serious?

268
00:12:21,519 --> 00:12:24,799
How could you bring this up
at the dinner table?

269
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,320
Yunchang.

270
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,399
I admit I was prejudiced
against you before.

271
00:12:28,399 --> 00:12:30,240
I went out of my way
to make things difficult.

272
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,440
For that,
I would like to offer an apology.

273
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:33,879
Let me be clear.

274
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:35,559
I approve of your marriage to Buyu.

275
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,159
And I agree as well.

276
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:39,759
This is absurd!

277
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:42,320
Marriage is a serious matter.
It can't be handled so recklessly.

278
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,159
Father.

279
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,279
There is something
I've been meaning to say.

280
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,879
That archaic family rule of ours

281
00:12:46,879 --> 00:12:48,120
should be abolished.

282
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,559
I agree.

283
00:12:49,679 --> 00:12:50,279
You!

284
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,279
Father,

285
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:52,919
rules are fixed,

286
00:12:52,919 --> 00:12:54,320
but people are not.

287
00:12:54,559 --> 00:12:56,600
Are you really going
to prioritize a stale tradition

288
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:58,679
over your own son's happiness?

289
00:12:59,039 --> 00:13:01,360
If Buyu loses Yunchang,

290
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:04,120
are you sure he will ever find
someone truly right for him again?

291
00:13:04,519 --> 00:13:06,559
If he spends
the rest of his life miserable,

292
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:07,919
how will you justify that

293
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,000
as his father?

294
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:17,879
You...

295
00:13:17,879 --> 00:13:18,759
- You...
- Chang.

296
00:13:29,679 --> 00:13:30,440
Fine.

297
00:13:31,399 --> 00:13:32,919
The young will find their own way.

298
00:13:34,399 --> 00:13:35,399
Get up, get up.

299
00:13:35,759 --> 00:13:37,320
I give you two my blessing.

300
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,120
Thank you, Father.

301
00:13:41,770 --> 00:13:42,759
Father gave his blessing!

302
00:13:42,759 --> 00:13:43,590
Go back and sit down.

303
00:13:47,810 --> 00:13:48,519
Come, have a seat.

304
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:49,320
- Please.
- All right.

305
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:49,919
Squire Mei.

306
00:13:51,759 --> 00:13:52,320
With this,

307
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,039
we have a double celebration today!

308
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,240
Come, let's have a toast as a family.

309
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:57,879
Come on.

310
00:13:57,879 --> 00:13:59,000
We're all in-laws now.

311
00:13:59,919 --> 00:14:00,679
Cheers!

312
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:07,919
Father.

313
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:09,279
We ran out of wine.

314
00:14:09,799 --> 00:14:10,440
Buyu.

315
00:14:10,799 --> 00:14:12,679
Go to the cellar
and bring up a good bottle.

316
00:14:12,679 --> 00:14:13,360
- On it.
- Buyu.

317
00:14:13,679 --> 00:14:14,440
Wait a moment.

318
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:16,039
I'll go instead.

319
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,039
Squire Mei,

320
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:21,240
would you care to join me?

321
00:14:24,399 --> 00:14:25,039
I'd love to.

322
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,840
I'd like to see your collection.

323
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,000
After you.

324
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:31,919
Please.

325
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:41,759
Let me peel this for you.

326
00:14:52,039 --> 00:14:52,799
Squire Mei.

327
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,679
Tell me what you think of this one.

328
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:57,625
(Wine)

329
00:15:07,519 --> 00:15:09,120
Impressive moves, Squire Mei.

330
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:10,919
As expected of

331
00:15:12,519 --> 00:15:15,679
the King of Thieves.

332
00:15:21,850 --> 00:15:25,125
♪Grudges and regrets
are like strong wine♪

333
00:15:25,163 --> 00:15:28,038
♪Drink it down and let it go♪

334
00:15:28,538 --> 00:15:34,256
♪An empty cup for our love and hate♪

335
00:15:35,438 --> 00:15:38,758
♪Tears blur a fate I can't control♪

336
00:15:38,888 --> 00:15:41,808
♪Let's drink until dawn♪

337
00:15:42,976 --> 00:15:48,216
♪Behind this mask, I'll never lie♪

338
00:15:49,438 --> 00:15:51,831
♪Every reunion feels like the first♪

339
00:15:51,831 --> 00:15:55,481
♪This hidden smile will never fade♪

340
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:59,040
♪One heart, standing by your side♪

341
00:15:59,138 --> 00:16:02,113
♪To the ends of time♪

342
00:16:02,113 --> 00:16:05,488
♪The moon traces your face♪

343
00:16:05,675 --> 00:16:09,263
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

344
00:16:09,263 --> 00:16:15,503
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

345
00:16:15,838 --> 00:16:19,053
♪A silent prayer in my soul♪

346
00:16:19,338 --> 00:16:22,876
♪Carrying my vow beneath the moon♪

347
00:16:23,163 --> 00:16:26,188
♪Hoping we never drift apart again♪

348
00:16:26,188 --> 00:16:29,288
♪On our way to forever♪

349
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:33,138
♪The moon traces your face♪

350
00:16:33,138 --> 00:16:36,498
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

351
00:16:36,688 --> 00:16:42,648
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

352
00:16:43,725 --> 00:16:53,365
♪Just to be with you♪
